cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on D2D communication and improving the performance of cellular links, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses pricing-based Stackelberg games, which are related to information theory and game theory.
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses matching theory and game theory to model the stable matching and pricing-based Stackelberg game, which falls under the scope of computer science and game theory.
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the cooperation between CEUs and D2D users, which can be seen as a social network problem.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the convenient content delivery directly among proximity users, which is related to multimedia.
